<TITLE> Sporting lose perfect record at rivals Benfica </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LISBON, Sept 28 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Sporting lost their perfect record in the Portuguese Premier League when they were beaten 2-0 by Benfica on Saturday. Unfancied Nacional Madeira, who host Estrela Amadora on Sunday, are the only side left with a 100 percent record. They and Sporting top the standings with nine points each. Champions Porto, who beat Pacos Ferreira 2-0 on Friday, and Benfica trail the two leaders by a point. After both teams wasted a number of chances in the first half of the Lisbon derby, Spaniard Jose Antonio Reyes put Benfica in front with an angled shot from a pass by Argentine midfielder Pablo Aimar in the 67th minute. Brazilian defender Sidnei sealed Benfica victory five minutes later when he headed home a freekick by Carlos Martins
